{"asset_id": "asset_cd0b5b5dd70ff81c0bfd1d34", "problem_id": "prob_59be777020dd0083125f3413", "asset_type": "text", "asset_role": "question_text_normalized", "source_uri": null, "storage_uri": "inline://prob_59be777020dd0083125f3413/question_normalized", "file_format": "txt", "file_size_bytes": 338, "width": null, "height": null, "sha256": "70d9c691a484b074c5acf3927b83b5a554cf938453cd946dc3a2fbf5f766912b", "perceptual_hash": null, "source_text_snapshot": "As shown in the figure, in the known $\\triangle ABC$, proceed with the following steps: \n(1) With centers at B and C, respectively, draw arcs with radii longer than $\\frac{1}{2}BC$, intersecting at points M and N; \n(2) Draw line MN intersecting AB at D, and connect CD. If $AC = 5$ and $AB = 12$, what is the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD$?", "normalized_text_snapshot": "As shown in the figure, in the known $\\triangle ABC$, proceed with the following steps: \n(1) With centers at B and C, respectively, draw arcs with radii longer than $\\frac{1}{2}BC$, intersecting at points M and N; \n(2) Draw line MN intersecting AB at D, and connect CD. If $AC = 5$ and $AB = 12$, what is the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD$?", "text_completeness_score": 0.8, "blur_score": null, "readability_score": null, "noise_score": null, "cropped_from_asset_id": null, "roi_bbox": null, "unit_normalization_map": [], "variable_aliases": [{"original": "As", "canonical": "As", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "in", "canonical": "in", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "the", "canonical": "the", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "ABC", "canonical": "ABC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "with", "canonical": "with", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "With", "canonical": "With", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "at", "canonical": "at", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "B", "canonical": "B", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "and", "canonical": "and", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "C", "ca